Stay hard!

No matter where you are from, how you look or what you believe, there is one thing we ALL have in common, we are all going to die. 

When are some of you going to stop letting yourself down? Too many of us are waiting for that magical moment when something clicks in our brains and the stars are aligned before we begin the process of becoming who we are truly supposed to be in this world. 

While that magical moment happens for some people, the majority of us need to realize that that moment will likely never arrive and we must be the ones to align the motherfucking stars ourselves! 

I believe the darkest days a person can have are when they look back on their life and realize they half-assed it and they can’t get that time back to do it again. 

You can’t keep saying to yourself you will do it tomorrow, because there comes a time when tomorrow will be gone. 

Mark my words- there will be a time in your life when all the noise is gone and it will become very quiet. That will be the time when you reflect. During that reflection, I hope that you lived life the way you wanted to live it and with no regrets. 

A lot of people for the New Year want to go on a diet, lose weight, start a new workout routine, stop drinking, etc. Same old bullshit every year. 

I would challenge you for the New Year to take time out for yourself. 
Quiet the noise. 
Reflect. 
Find what you truly want out of life. 
Stop starting things that you know you are going to stop anyway. 
Stop wasting time. 
Make sure all of your time is spent with the proper people and on the path leading you to your ultimate destination.

In a world that continues to get weaker and weaker every year, we’ve created a community of people who detest mediocrity. 

Marketing people are tripped out over the fact that my books, Never Finished and Can’t Hurt Me, are doing so well doing so little marketing. 

I have said for many years I would rather have one hard motherfucker than 20 weak ones. Out of the 7.8 million people I have following me on social media, I truly believe the majority of you are that one hard motherfucker who is trying to get better, trying to find more, and isn’t wasting time on things that don’t concern them or they can not change. 

The marketing guy was telling me how much money is spent by the publishing houses and authors trying to promote their books, some have put $1 million in marketing spend behind their books. I have never spent $1 on marketing, advertising or promotions. 

When you have a community as strong as the one we have built, if the book is good and helping people, I knew that this group would find a way to tell others about it. You see, at the end of the day, we are all in the business of trying to help people get better.

A lot of people who are doing all of this marketing miss that point. They want to put ads in front of you, promote their stories on your feed, appear on countless tv shows, etc., hoping to draw you to their book. While I have done two podcasts and put it on my social media, I only did that so you know the book exists. 

What people fail to realize is that most marketing is done by the people. If you have a shitty product that doesn’t help them out you can market it all day, the people will not endorse it nor will they suggest to others that they buy it. 

I love the fact that a lot of you are waking up tired of who you once were and doing even when you don’t want to do. 

I may not be sponsored in the traditional way by any major brands, companies, or products and have financed all of my projects on my own, but I do believe I am sponsored by all of you and have a responsibility to keep shit real and authentic. 

Who needs a sponsor when I am sponsored by all of you?! Stay hard!

FYI- there is an asshole posing as me on LinkedIn and possibly other platforms as well who is taking money from people in exchange for a supposed call with me. 

I am not even on LinkedIn but, more importantly, I would never offer to call someone only if I was paid to do so. I have made plenty of calls and videos for people - all for free.  I would never ask to be paid to do these things. 

That said, if you are communicating with someone about a request such as this and considering paying money, it is not me. Please do send your exchanges with this individual(s) to info@davidgoggins.com as we are pursuing legal action. 

I apologize that people suck but they do. 

Stay hard!

There are a lot of naturally gifted individuals out there who make their craft look easy. Things just come naturally, almost effortlessly, to them so much so that smooth success becomes the expected. 

I see this a lot in sports whether it be fighting, basketball, tennis or football, as well as those naturally gifted in school, when I watch these naturally gifted people in their arena. You can immediately tell when they start bumping up against the end of their talent. You see this once effortless human being now look like a deer caught in the headlights. 

These individuals get trapped in their heads and are unable to figure a way out of the situation. They don’t know what is going on because they have never met this challenge before. 

To me, it is very obvious what is happening- they have a talent problem. Their talent took them all the way there. While they may have worked hard to get there, they never worked past their talent. 

These people may advance quickly in their field but unless they learn how to stay focused and positive when things go badly, unless they learn to become master of their emotions through hard work, discipline and faith in themselves, and detach from the outcome, they will eventually smack face first into a glass ceiling. 

While natural talent gives you an extreme edge, talent alone will never lift you sky high. Talent might be the very thing that keeps you from reaching your true potential. 

You must learn to work past your talent so when the hard times come, your mind knows what to do when your talent runs out. 

#NeverFinished #canthurtme

It’s amazing how many people have no guilt & are totally emotionless when it comes finding more of themselves. They wake up, walk around, & go to bed with zero accountability. They can spend an entire day not working on improving themselves. Not because they physically or mentally couldn’t rather because they just didn’t want to. An entire day wasted & yet they are not thinking about the consequences & cumulative effect of wasted days. 

Since we can’t say shit in this world nor can we hold people accountable, we have morphed into a society where we just encourage everyone to be happy with who they are and the status quo. 

DON’T TWIST MY MESSAGE- I am not saying to not be happy with you are. If there is something you literally CAN’T improve through hard work & effort… wait a minute, here I am now trying to explain what I mean so that I don’t offend people who are looking to be offended!!! 

The bottom line is this- no one is happy being behind the power curve in any situation in life but it has become very acceptable to ignore the voice of hard work and discipline. It is easy to ignore it because that it what society is pushing nowadays. 

In my life, I was behind the power curve in countless situations- my weight, my learning, my self-discipline, etc. Thank God I grew up in a generation that preached “work harder” rather than just accepting the cards that I was dealt. 

A lot of you are fucked nowadays because the message being preached is just the opposite. “That’s just how you were born”- be happy about it rather than attempt to outwork it! Be happy just meeting the standard!

Just know that the very people who are preaching this to you and telling you that it is ok to be mediocre, are the very same people who will not hire you because they don’t want an underachiever on their team! They are just saying what they are told to say even though they don’t truly believe it. 

It’s easy to see why I am misunderstood by so many people because my message is almost obsolete nowadays. 

Many of you will continue to fail if you do not figure out how to do just because you need to do. No one gives a fuck what you want to do! 

Stay hard!

This is the work, The Only, by @milanablackman. She has done a few of these already including one of the  @joerogan and @joeroganexperience which features some of his past guests as well as one of the late @anthonybourdain. 

“The Only” tells some of my life story. If you haven’t read either Can’t Hurt Me or Never Finished, some of these illustrations and the name of the piece may not make sense but to others it will be very clear. 

For those of you who read Can’t Hurt Me, you might recognize the image to be the same as is featured on the cover of the book however she uses my uniform as the story board of my life. 

You can see me as a young child, the 297lb version of me, the accountability mirror, the cookie jar, the ribbon rack on the uniform pocket to my smokejumping experience in the bottom right corner of the picture and many other key life moments in between. 

What is most amazing about this was the way she put the drawing together. She read Can’t Hurt Me, listened to podcasts and went on long runs (along with other things) in an effort to get deep inside my head to bring out my story within the piece itself. 

She is a great artist but I am even more impressed with how she attacks her work. While she was doing this piece, she hadn’t read my latest book, Never Finished, yet was able to capture the essence of what that book also reveals and that is that no matter how much you have achieved, we should constantly be trying to evolve into our best self. In the picture she illustrates that with the barrel and then the astronaut on the moon. The barrel signifies how I came from the bottom of the barrel and my drive keeps me reaching for the moon. 

Stay hard!

Stay hard!

With the recent launch of my second book Never Finished, already having sold 800,000 copies in 7 weeks, and Can’t Hurt Me, my first book, just crossing the 5 million copies sold mark…I thought it was fitting to again share this @goal.cast video that now has over 100 million views globally.

Stay hard!

There’s a section during one of the podcasts in the Never Finished audiobook where my mom and I go deep into some of the trauma my father caused. It’s one of the most powerful things maybe ever in audiobooks because she is sharing her story in her words, not just from my point of view and how I experienced it. 

No one is reading it, it wasn’t rehearsed, it was 35 minutes of this-is-who-the-fuck-I-am…take it or leave it! It took decades for her to get to a point in her life where she could talk openly and honestly about it. By finally owning that trauma her life has now finally changed for the better. 

There is something very empowering about owning your failures, your faults, your imperfections, the lies we tell ourselves and others, and most of all, your past traumas. 

We put way too much value in what others think about us. No matter how big you are in the world, or how small, and everything in between, you are not a perfect person. So, why do you think you have to hide your imperfections? 

Most of us look at being judged as a bad thing. While it doesn’t feel great, you have to know that the very people who are judging you are also imperfect and flawed people. But, the mind has a great way of playing tricks on us. 

When we are fucked up, we believe we are the only ones that are messed up. Peel back from that tunnel vision. Look around you. We are all trying to tight-rope life. Don’t ever let anybody in this world make you feel a certain way. The only thing you should be ashamed of in your life is if you are not trying to fix the problems that you have. 

Stay hard!  #neverfinished

Someone recently tagged me in this video.

When this man challenged me to an arm wrestling competition, he was comfortably seated in his chair. I could tell he was a massive man but when he stood up, he was literally a fucking giant.  He was a 6’7” 330lb former Offensive Tackle at OSU. 

I will never forget when I grabbed his hand, I remember thinking this must be what a bear’s paw feels like. 

The takeaway is this- he called me out in front of a room full of people and even though I don’t arm wrestle, I knew if I could just hang with him for a few seconds, I would get in his head. You know when a person challenges you to something, it is something that they are good at so I knew that he thought that he was going to destroy me but, as we all know, YOU DON’T KNOW ME, SON!!!!

A lot of times all we have to do is create doubt in the opposition. That doubt takes away their confidence and levels the playing field which creates an opportunity on which to capitalize. If you are not sure you are going to win at something, make sure you stay in it long enough to make your opponent doubt themselves! 

Stay hard!

Stay hard!

It’s so easy to be great nowadays.

A lot of people want to level up in this world simply because they think they deserve it or are entitled to it. 

For those who truly do want to level up, one of the best ways of doing it is by sometimes seeking out opportunities where misery is calling your name. 

The more miserable the task is in front of you, the harder you must become. This isn’t some macho bullshit, this is a proven tactic that works. So don’t wish it away, welcome its presence. When you stop thinking that something sucks, it does.

You shouldn’t want to be normal. The standard for normal in today’s world has changed. Normal is just the new word for weak. 

Don’t get it twisted - while I am talking about working out in the video, this definitely isn’t just about working out. 

Very few people go after anything anymore like there is no tomorrow. Those who do are the outliers and are often looked at or perceived as crazy. 

They are not crazy, they’re just not you. 

Like I always say, my message isn’t for everybody so if you get offended, I am not for you. I am for those people who are searching for greatness inside themselves. 

Stay hard!

I am not who I used to be…some might say I am a little bit better. While I am not as fast as I once was, my endurance of the mind is far superior to what it used to be. I know exactly where the mind is going to go before it goes there. 

This group of guys has been wanting to run with me for a long time so I got tired of them asking. While they say they want to run with me, I know they really want to kick my ass. That said, they committed a cardinal sin. I asked them how far they wanted to run when we were about 3 miles into the run. They saw I was limping to start and my gait was a little fucked up so I looked slow and old. So, their answer was “as far as you want to go.” I simply replied “Roger that!” There is a start line to quitting and I know exactly where that starts and I am going to take all these motherfuckers there! 

Three things they didn’t know,  my knee is still trying to reset after surgery, hence the limp, and I don’t get warmed up or find my stride until about 45 minutes into my run. Last thing, when you see me wearing this black pack around my waist, it means you are in for a long fucking day! 

I found out a long time that when the distance is unknown, it truly fucks with people. As we got to about the 20 mile mark, they knew where we started and got a little happy as we were coming upon that starting point. When we continued to run past that starting point, their happiness turned to sadness. 

My limp was gone, my breathing was easy, and I knew they had to be thinking “we are running with a guy who can run 250 miles nonstop.” All that made me laugh inside as we passed what they thought was the finish line.

Never underestimate a person who trains every single day of their life. They might just know something you don’t! 

Stay hard!

There is something that you need to get in your head. No one, and I mean no one, is ever going to feel sorry for you. There may be some people who sit there and appease you but there is very little that anyone can do for you. 

You and you alone are the only one who can get you out of your darkness. We often wonder why we can’t get out of the darkness that we are in. There is a simple answer to it- you are choosing to stay in it. 

I know your response to this is “I am trying, I am trying to get out of the darkness and find my better self.” Like most people, your trying is too inconsistent. Therefore the little gains that you made while you were trying, were likely all given back and then some due to your inconsistency. 

A lot of us are only disciplined when someone is in our face on a daily basis. We need that accountability person in our lives. The second they go away, we go away. 

A lot of you think it is ok to be where you are and society tells you as much, mediocrity is too often rewarded.

I am speaking from experience. It is hard to judge yourself nowadays and see where you stand and how you measure up because the world is grading us all on a massive curve. Like in school, the curve is off of the highest grade. The problem today is that the world is grading us on a “C-“ curve, therefore a “D” doesn’t seem so bad! You think you are doing just fine. 

When I was lazy in school, living that mediocre life, when I got my “D’s”, I was happy because I knew a “D” was passing. That is how pathetic the standard was that I set for myself. The bar was so fucking low. 

As I look around me now, I see a lot of people happy with a “D” in life. 

Stay hard!

The road to success isn’t always a clear and smooth path. We are all being tested in life and those tests aren’t easy for any of us. 

Many people assume I go into things without thinking but it is quite contrary. 

When I finally pulled my head out of my ass and realized what I truly wanted in life, I had to sit back and think about what it would take for me to get there. I had to measure my want. 

What that means is I had to ask myself “What am I willing to put myself through to achieve it? What am I willing to give up in order to achieve it?”

I went all in on me. I knew that there would be a lot of bumps and bruises along the way. Some over-use injuries and a lot of dark times. But, for me, it was all worth it. My want was so great that I didn’t give a fuck what it came with. Sometimes your want isn’t that great and doesn’t warrant that kind of dedication. 

It makes some people feel good to think that I’m all fucked up. It’s almost like I-told-you-so type shit. See, he ran too much, didn’t rest enough, etc. While my body is fucked up and I have had my fair share of injuries, I’ve always worked myself back and my body still works better than most healthy bodies because my mind is trained different than most. 

Too many people talk too much about giving yourself a break. More people need to talk about giving more and pushing harder.  20 years ago, people would see my effort as “Damn, that guy truly wants it bad!” Nowadays my effort is looked at, like, “Look at what he’s doing to himself?!”

Many of you haven’t found what you truly want in your life. Once you do, I suggest you figure out how to give your all.  No, I’m not saying fuck yourself up! There’s a very thin line in between we all must walk if we are looking for true greatness in ourselves. The real problem isn’t the fear of a fucked up body. It’s your fear of the effort required to truly give your all.

For many of us, we must be willing to live on that edge. Yes, you might die with a used up body but it will be a body that truly lived and conquered! 

Stay hard!

There is one thing in life we all have to realize… you are not always going to be the favorite. Sometimes you won’t get the love, the attention, or the respect you feel you deserve or have earned. 

You have to learn to be the person who is fine with that. 

A lot of people are going to want to see you lose and see you fall on your face, especially if you are good at what you do. 

Stop being a person who looks for the attention, the praise, and the applause. 

You have to know that you put the work in, not just on your body, but most importantly, on your mind. 

When you are walking into these underdog situations, it is important that your mind is covered in Kevlar. 

While the crowd and the opponent want to take your heart, it is important that you recognize that you have the opportunity to not just defeat one person but to defeat many. 

In doing so, you will gain the respect you deserve. All the training in the world doesn’t matter if you have failed to train the most important weapon in the world, your mind. 

Respect to all of those who find themselves in this situation and are willing to go at it alone! A real warrior finds great pleasure in knowing that just one sword can take out many! 

Stay hard!

I had the honor of working with @jonnybones and his amazing team last week. Truly amazing how they left no stone unturned in their preparation for this fight and it showed by his performance. I also got a chance to sit with my boy @cameronrhanes thanks to @joerogan … I was obviously jacked to see Bones put that work in and get it done in quick fashion!

You know this is going to be one of my best friends for life when the first day we meet, he takes me out for a 35 mile race, a brutal gym workout, and teaches me how to shoot a bow all on Day 1 of friendship! 

@cameronrhanes is part of a small group of people- and when I say small, I mean VERY small! So many people out here are telling you to get up early, go hard, grind, get uncomfortable, and tons of other overused catch phrases. 

Most of them are full of shit. All you have to do is look at their out of shape bodies to see just how out of date their resumes are! 

I have been looking for decades for people who don’t use excuses like age, past successes, schedules, weather, etc., and truly love the Day One, Week One mentality. 

I have seen firsthand that Cam is one of them. Mad respect! 

Very few people push me to the point where I have to kill David Goggins and bring out Goggins!

It’s inevitable that we all will encounter hard times. A lot of us are very prepared for the hard times that we will be faced with but still quit during those hard times. 

Most people when they quit during those hard times brush it off by saying “it wasn’t meant to be” but very few dissect that hard time and the real reason they quit. 

If you did dissect it, you would probably figure out that you were kicking ass for 99% of that time. You might have lost focus for just one second or two and that is all it takes. 

If you are not able to gain control of those seconds, where something triggers a fight or flight response from you, you will lose every time. 

Like I say, many dreams die while suffering. It’s not so much the suffering that gets us, it’s how we respond to it. 

The one second decision has helped me through a lot of hard times. In that one second that you want to quit, you have to regain perspective and not allow the voice of weakness and doubt to creep in. 

The dialogue that you will hear in the worst of times will be unfamiliar to you because chances are you haven’t been in this or similar situations often. It’s ok, we have to remind ourselves that’s probably why we signed up or chose to be in this very trying situation. 

Your mind is a weapon. Don’t allow difficult times strip you of the most powerful weapon you will ever have. 

Stay hard!

If some moderator takes this post down, it is a disservice to society. We can’t keep hiding this shit from people. 

Growing up I had people calling me “Nigger” and most of the time it wasn’t to my face. We didn’t have social media back then so instead of being a coward online, they would write it in my notebooks, leave messages in my locker and even spray paint it on my car. 

Even more hurtful was when people tried to tell me that it didn’t happen and it doesn’t exist. Thank God for my high school principal otherwise I would have not have been able to share those experiences as he was the only one brave enough to go on record admitting that it happened. 

You would be shocked at the hundreds of emails I get daily from kids who are unsure how to handle the hate they encounter at school and online. Many of them feel like they want to die and are desperately seeking help. An email response from me can’t fix what they are dealing with- it takes countless, real conversations. 

A lot of you are afraid to show this kind of message to your kids and want to hide and protect them from this kind of hate. I strongly suggest showing them stuff like this - prepare them for the world they are going to experience. They might not be called “Nigger” but they will find another word that is equally offensive. 

The worst thing I have ever experienced was when a young man reached out to me on email saying that he wanted to kill himself. He was getting bullied and didn’t know how to handle it. Sad thing is that I responded to it months too late. 

We hide too much from our kids and are trying to create some perfect world for them so when the hard times come- and they are coming!- they have no idea how to handle it. They can’t see beyond it. 

I am sharing this with you to let you know that you are not alone. I am 48 years old and have been experiencing this for 48 years. This post is amateur compared to the things I have endured and yet I have not only survived the hate, I have thrived in spite of it.

NEVER BE ANONYMOUS! 

Don’t let hate, bullying, not fitting in, being overweight, stuttering, not being popular, not being smart, etc., make you feel like you just want to hide out and be anonymous. 

We are not made to be anonymous! We are made to stand tall and stand out!

Stay hard!

There is a massive infestation of weak people in today’s world. Just by sheer numbers, the weak voice is becoming the voice of the world. 

The weak have tactics to silence the strong-minded. One of their tactics is isolation. 

Very few people are equipped to handle the isolation that they will have to endure in order to maintain their beliefs. Eventually the strong-minded succumb to the weak. 

Before succumbing to the weak completely, there is a phase where they start to lose themselves. They start speaking out of both sides of their mouth and when they do that, they don’t stand for anything. They see what the majority is talking about and what they believe in and they simply follow suit.

I saw it my whole military career. Whenever people would be checking in to different commands, the leadership would get together and ask for an opinion on the people coming in.
Rather than take the time to formulate their own opinion, they take the cowardly way out and accept what some other person said as truth. 

This is one of many signs of a bad leader. Instead of accepting someone else’s word as truth, you should realize that the same person you let dictate your opinion is just as likely to run their mouth about you when you aren’t around. 

Every now and then you will find yourself speaking out of the other side of your mouth about what you truly believe in but only to the right people. You aren’t as loud as you used to be and eventually the more you practice these weak habits of saying what you want to say behind closed doors, pretty soon you become a bobblehead. Your mouth is completely sewn shut and all you can do is listen and shake your head yes and agree with whatever the weak have said. 

The goal is to make everybody think the same, act the same, believe the same and talk the same. Sadly, it is actually fucking working! Very few have a fucking opinion on which they are willing to risk acceptance or fitting in! 

Stay hard!

I just did the Chips N’ Caviar Podcast. This will not be my typical motivational podcast, it’s more of a go-fuck-yourself podcast! 

I have been hearing a lot of lies and shit for years about my military career, my service, and my skills as an operator. 

The legend of the Navy SEALs is what made me who I am. I had to change everything about myself just to get in the door. I had been a piece of shit and a liar about who I wanted to be instead of telling the truth about who I was. I had to accept a lot of bad things about myself and slowly found the courage to change it to live up to that legend.

What I ultimately found is that the legend is no more than a myth. Now to be clear, there are some bad motherfuckers within that community and some of them are my very best friends. And while I don’t know all of them, sadly a lot of the ones I do know, act just like the examples you will see in the podcast.

When you hear Navy SEAL, don’t associate me with that myth. You are giving them way too much fucking credit. I worked my natural ass off to build character and continue to bust my ass every fucking day, living that Day One, Week One mentality. It’s not some marketing bullshit like a lot of them will sell you. 

While I am flawed like a motherfucker, you will never see me lie about somebody in an effort to take them down to hurt their reputation and who they are. These people were purposeful in their actions. As I say, Roger Fucking That! 

I never wanted to do this nor go there. I want to always stay true to my mission of helping people do and get better because I know how hard this world is out here. 

Long story short, this Navy SEAL did a podcast with this guy running his mouth so now it is time that these motherfuckers hear it from my me. I have hard documents to provide hard facts. 

Never let a motherfucker defame your character, your hard work and dedication to being better. Several people told me to “take the high road,” “don’t worry about it,” “you know the truth, etc. 

So many motherfuckers take that high road that it’s too busy up there right now so I am going back to old school Goggins where there are no roads. There are just hard truths and fuck yous.

I didn’t know @aaronsingerman and I didn’t know about this featured clip from his podcast where I was used as clickbait until it was brought to my attention.

What would you do if you knew success was 100% guaranteed? What would your life look like? 

Most people don’t aggressively pursue their dreams or audacious goals because there is a slim chance they won’t make it - the slightest chance of failure keeps them from going for it. The slightest chance of failure keeps them from complete and lasting fulfillment. People are willing to give it all up and live a mediocre, risk-free safe life rather than  fail.

While it is true that no one is 100%, most of the reasons we are not is because we have buried parts of our selves in the dark crevices of our mind. What we bury are our past failures, our imperfections, our abusive childhoods, and all of the things about us that we don’t like. We bury them because we don’t want to deal with or face them so we store them away. 

They are locked within the basement, within the attic, within the dungeons of our mind. The spaces we are afraid to enter - there are spiders, it hasn’t been cleaned in a while so there are cobwebs, the lightswitches don’t work in those compartments, it’s dark and creepy. 

You want someone to go in there with you but no one can. No one can go into that space but yourself. It’s the loneliness in and fear of going back to these places that prevent you from doing it. The reason why you have to do this alone is because these are the experiences and trauma that you endured alone. 

But it is in those very spaces that you will find your very best self and the extra % you are looking for. 

So what parts and how much of you and your mind have you buried? 10%? 20%? 50%? 

Know that even when you have the courage to go back in, fix yourself, and get the extra percentage, you still might not trust that you are enough. You must know that you are more than good enough! Stay hard!

A lot of people asked me to show them a sample calisthenic workout.

This is my favorite go-to and I I call it “Nickels and Dimes.” For this workout, I  do 5 pull-ups immediately followed by 10 push-ups thus the name. 

I will do this as a standalone workout for an hour or two hours, etc.

When I do this for an hour or two, I will pace it so that I do two sets on the minute- so 2 sets of pull-ups and 2 sets of push-ups on the minute. In one hour, I will do 600 pull-ups and 1200 push-ups. 

If it is a shorter workout, you want to go at a faster pace to maximize the time. 

You want to get to a point where you can make the transition without any break at all and go immediately from one to the other like I did in the video. 

Again, the ideal pace is to do two sets on the minute- 2 sets of pull-ups and 2 sets of push-ups on the minute. 

Whatever number of pull-ups you do, double it for the push-ups. So if you do 3 pull-ups, do 6 push-ups, etc. Choose a number that works for you, one that you can hold for the designated workout time. 

Some of you may be working with pennies rather than nickels and dimes. A lot of you may need to get loans from the bank before you’re ready for the money! We all start somewhere!

There have been more times in my life than I can count when I thought I was done, it was over, I had nothing left to give.  Whether it was from fatigue, or I was in my head, injuries, etc., BUT there was always more to give and always more to find. 

For those of you who have quit like I have in the past, you realize once you have quit that in face you did have more to give. It is those people who are able to find more even under the harshest conditions who succeed. 

We live in a world where people want to see you fail, many of you may disagree with that statement, oh but I know all too well! When you are on top of a mountain, people want to push you off! They are waiting for your mistakes. They are waiting for the moment when you can’t take another step. They are smiling at your failure. 

For those people who want to see you fail, what they don’t understand is this… they are at the bottom of the mountain where there is tons of oxygen which allows them to run their mouth. 

For those few who have the guts to climb, the higher you climb, the less oxygen there is which means the less you talk. The air gets thin the higher you guy so you make a conscious choice to conserve your energy knowing that you want to get to the top of the mountain. And the air at the top of that mountain is very thin. Very little needs to be said while you are climbing the mountain let alone standing at the top! 

Remember this: all those days you don’t want to do something, all those days where injury plagues your mind and all those days when fatigue is keeping you in bed, you, my friend, are making a motherfucker happy by giving in to those feelings. 

This video captures a proud moment for me because 99% of my life, I have been fighting the voice of “just stop, you don’t need to do this today!” I didn’t set out for awards. recognition, fame or success, I was simply trying to change how I felt about myself.

I get attacked on social media every single day from people I don’t even know. I have never met them but I clearly rub them the wrong way. As a man, there is nothing weaker than judging someone who you personally do not know.

Social media has taught me that insecure and jealous people often look at others who have what they don’t & project their own feelings of inadequacy in the form of hate. I talk about this a lot on the @hubermanlab podcast. You can not allow that energy shift to happen!

I don’t speak about religion, politics, race, gender, or sexuality. I don’t judge anyone for who they are, who they want to be and what they believe in. 
I care only about helping people find every bit of themselves that they can- period. My books, Can’t Hurt Me and Never Finished, have sold millions of copies and changed millions of lives with their messages and takeaways built solely around helping people get better and yet I still receive this hate. 

My last video was something I didn’t even put up. I didn’t say a word in it and my face couldn’t even be seen. So those who usually get worked up because of my cussing didn’t even get that, they simply saw a man minding his business while grinding on a desolate empty road. It is imperative for your mental health that you understand jealous, weak, and insecure people’s minds. The more you understand their minds, the more clear the motivation behind their hateful actions and words will be. 

Don’t allow the people with the weakest minds and least self-respect affect your mental health! 

Know that the next soul you take without even trying will be theirs just by being you!
